Problem Name: Allocate Books
Difficulty: Medium
Platform: Coding Ninjas / Interview Bit

Problem Description:
Given an array arr of integers, where arr[i] represents the number of pages in the i-th book. Given k number of students. Allocate books to students such that:

Each student gets at least one book

Books allocated to each student are contiguous (i.e., if a student gets books from index i to j, they must be consecutive in the array)

Allocation should be done in such a way that the maximum number of pages assigned to any student is minimized

All books must be allocated

If it's not possible to allocate books to k students, return -1.

Example 1:

text
Input: arr = [12, 34, 67, 90], k = 2
Output: 113
Explanation: 
Allocation can be done in following ways:
[12] and [34, 67, 90] → Max pages = max(12, 191) = 191
[12, 34] and [67, 90] → Max pages = max(46, 157) = 157
[12, 34, 67] and [90] → Max pages = max(113, 90) = 113  ← Minimum among all
Therefore minimum possible maximum pages = 113
Example 2:

text
Input: arr = [5, 10, 30, 20, 15], k = 3
Output: 35
Explanation: 
Optimal allocation: [5, 10], [30], [20, 15] → Max pages = max(15, 30, 35) = 35
Constraints:

1 ≤ N ≤ 10^5

1 ≤ arr[i] ≤ 10^6

1 ≤ k ≤ N

